# AlexOS Vision

Version: 1.0
Status: Official Vision Document
Project: AlexOS
Author: Nicolás Revilla & Alex (OpenAI)

---

# What is AlexOS?

AlexOS is a modern, touch-first personal operating system designed for Raspberry Pi touch displays.

It is not a Linux desktop replacement.

It is not another dashboard.

It is a complete personal command center that becomes the first thing the user sees every day.

AlexOS centralizes productivity, study, home automation, personal servers, communication, media, AI and daily information into one beautiful, fast and intuitive interface.

Its purpose is to eliminate friction and make information available instantly.

---

# Mission

Create the most enjoyable and useful dashboard ever built for Raspberry Pi.

Not because it has the most features.

Because every feature feels carefully designed.

---

# Vision

Imagine waking up.

You touch the screen.

Instead of opening five different applications...

Everything is already there.

Calendar.

Tasks.

Music.

Weather.

Servers.

Docker.

Notifications.

Email.

Study.

Your room.

Your Raspberry Pis.

Everything.

AlexOS is the digital home of its user.

---

# Philosophy

AlexOS follows one simple principle.

Every interaction should feel effortless.

The interface should disappear.

The information should remain.

---

# Design Principles

Minimal.

Elegant.

Fast.

Touch-first.

Zero clutter.

Consistent.

Modern.

Alive.

Every animation has a purpose.

Every button exists for a reason.

Every screen feels calm.

---

# User Experience

AlexOS should never feel like software.

It should feel like a living desk companion.

Morning:

"Good morning, Nicolás ☀️"

Night:

"Good night 🌙"

Exam tomorrow:

"You have your C1 exam tomorrow. Good luck!"

Birthday:

A unique celebration animation.

Server offline:

A discreet notification.

Everything feels contextual.

Never random.

