💻 Servers

📡 Network

🎵 Media

🤖 Artificial Intelligence

🏠 Smart Room

📈 Finance

🚗 Vehicle

⚙️ Settings

---

# Modular Architecture

Everything inside AlexOS is a module.

Nothing is hardcoded.

Clock.

Weather.

Spotify.

Docker.

Gmail.

WhatsApp.

Calendar.

Notes.

Everything.

Modules can be installed, updated or removed independently.

---

# Long Term Vision

AlexOS starts as a personal project.

Later it may become:

An open-source ecosystem.

A plugin platform.

A Raspberry Pi operating environment.

A community project.

The architecture must support this possibility from day one.

---

# What AlexOS is NOT

Not a website.

Not a collection of widgets.

Not a browser dashboard.

Not a clone of Home Assistant.

Not a Linux desktop.

AlexOS is its own product.

---

# Performance Goals

Cold boot under 10 seconds.

UI at 60 FPS.

Touch latency below 50 ms.

Animations below 250 ms.

Instant navigation.

Low RAM usage.

Optimized for Raspberry Pi 5.

---

# Future

AI assistant.

Voice control.

Plugin Store.

Themes.

Widgets.

Mobile companion app.

Desktop version.

Cloud sync.

Automation engine.

Community modules.

---

# Final Statement

AlexOS is not designed to impress people for five minutes.

It is designed to become the application its creator opens every single day.

If a feature does not improve daily life, it does not belong in AlexOS.
